overview: Before her untimely death from multiple sclerosis in 1987, renowned cellist Jacqueline Du Pre won classical audiences in the 1960s and '70s with her robust and lively approach to musicianship, a testament to her innate genius and deep affinity for the pieces she played. See her face Brahms's cello sonatas, Beethoven's "Sonata No. 3 in A, Op. 69" (with husband Daniel Barenboim on piano), Elgar's "Cello Concerto in E minor, Op. 85" and many others.
title: Jacqueline Du Pre: Legend
